article.headline: Maine 67, New Hampshire 53
article.story: DURHAM, N.H. (AP) -- Led by Ernest Turner's 17 points, Maine ended New Hampshire's four-win streak with a 67-53 victory Thursday. Maine (7-10, 2-4) jumped out to a 9-0 lead and twice led by as many as 10 points in the first half. The UNH offense emerged with less than 12 minutes in the half as Brandon Odom sank two free throws cutting Maine' advantage to 22-17. Blagoj Janev converted a 3-pointer and slimmed Maine's lead to 26-25. But Turner scored Maine's final three baskets of the half for a 33-29 lead. In the second half Chris Vetrano's 3-pointer pulled New Hampshire (6-12, 3-4) within four points, 38-34. Jon Sheets sank a trey that began a 9-2 Maine run, maintaining a double-digit lead for the rest of the game, by as many as 18 points. Janev scored 13 points for UNH while Odom had 11.
